        "content": "<p>This is a topic to share LWN articles about Rust for Linux, Rust and other Rust-related topics.</p>\n<p>A list of articles from 2024 so far:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://lwn.net/Articles/958072/\">Rust and C filesystem APIs</a> (January 15, 2024)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://lwn.net/Articles/958792/\">Defining the Rust 2024 edition</a> (January 29, 2024)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://lwn.net/Articles/967049/\">A memory model for Rust code in the kernel</a> (April 3, 2024)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://lwn.net/Articles/970216/\">Rust for embedded Linux kernels</a> (April 23, 2024)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://lwn.net/Articles/970186/\">Existential types in Rust</a> (April 24, 2024)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://lwn.net/Articles/970565/\">Giving Rust a chance for in-kernel codecs</a> (April 26, 2024)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://lwn.net/Articles/976355/\">Removing GFP_NOFS</a> (June 5, 2024)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://lwn.net/Articles/978738/\">Rust for filesystems</a> (June 21, 2024)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://lwn.net/Articles/982868/\">Standards for use of unsafe Rust in the kernel</a> (August 14, 2024)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>From time to time there are also posts (i.e. not full articles) that may be interesting to share, since they sometimes contain interesting discussions in the comments, such as the Rust release posts or the recent one about the project goals:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://lwn.net/Articles/966205/\">Rust 1.77.0 released</a> (March 21, 2024)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://lwn.net/Articles/972191/\">Rust 1.78.0 released</a> (May 2, 2024)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://lwn.net/Articles/978323/\">Rust 1.79.0 released</a> (June 13, 2024)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://lwn.net/Articles/983265/\">Rust 1.80.0 released</a> (July 25, 2024)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://lwn.net/Articles/985296/\">Rust Project goals for 2024</a> (August 12, 2024).</li>\n</ul>",
